[b]MIDAS 2.0 [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
MIDAS 2.0 plots an anchored MIDAS support/resistance curve — a launch-anchored, volume-weighted average price — and adds a true topfinder/bottomfinder accelerated curve that gives an accelerated estimate of where a launched move runs out of fuel. It answers two questions: where is price relative to value, and how far has this move travelled toward its projected end. It is a location and exhaustion tool, not a buy/sell signal generator.

[b]The MIDAS curve[/b]
[list]
[*]Anchored at a manual time, the daily open, or an automatic swing pivot
[*]Auto anchors re-seed from the real pivot bar, not the lagging confirmation bar — or, in Confirmed display mode, only from the bar the pivot is actually known live
[*]Volume-weighted standard-deviation bands or ATR bands at two multiples
[*]In an uptrend price tends to ride above a curve launched from a swing low (dynamic support); in a downtrend below one from a swing high (dynamic resistance)
[/list]

[b]Topfinder / Bottomfinder[/b]
[list]
[*]When a trend accelerates away from its MIDAS curve, an accelerated curve is fitted that catches back up to price and projects where the move ends
[*]The fit is solved in closed form so the curve passes through the most recent same-direction swing
[*]The dashboard reports progress (d/D) toward the projected end; at the warn threshold the move is flagged as exhausting
[/list]

[b]Context markers[/b]
[list]
[*]Stretched-from-value — price rejected at the outer band in the prevailing bias
[*]MIDAS reclaim — price reclaimed (or lost) the curve, annotated with a 0-5 Reclaim Quality Score (stretch, close strength, volume, structure break, exhaustion bonus — context only, never a filter)
[*]TBF late move — the launched move reached the topfinder/bottomfinder warn threshold
[/list]
These are setup-level context, not entries.

[b]Dashboard[/b]
[list]
[*]Bias, distance from value, band zone
[*]Topfinder/bottomfinder progress and exhaustion state
[*]MIDAS value, bars since the anchor, and whether volume is available (falls back to equal-weighted price if not)
[/list]

